    <title>[Review ongoing] Manage legends</title>
    <section>
        <title>About legends</title>
        <para>You can create your own legend to make sure that maps created in the GIS app are
            meaningful.</para>
        <note>
            <para><?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160921T163643+0200" comment="Verify with SME if this information is still necessary."?>Continuous<?oxy_comment_end?>
                legends are supposed to end and start on the same value, for example 0-50 and 50-80.
                The GIS app automatically take care of
                <?oxy_comment_start author="Home" timestamp="20160413T120439+0200" comment="Of what?"?>this<?oxy_comment_end?>.
                Do not try to do this yourself by setting legends to for example 0-50 and 51-80.
                This will cause a usually unwanted gap in your legend set.</para>
        </note>
        <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Maintenance</emphasis> app, you manage the following
            legend objects:</para>
        <table frame="all">
            <title>Legend objects in the Maintenance app</title>
            <tgroup cols="2">
                <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Object type</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Available functions</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Legend</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Create, edit, clone, delete, show details and translate</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Create a legend</title>
        <note>
            <para>It is not allowed to have gaps in a legend.</para>
            <para>It is not allowed to have overlapping legend items.</para>
        </note>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Maintenance</emphasis> app and click <emphasis
                        role="bold">Other</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold"
                    >Legend</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click the add
                    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160510T112410+0200" comment="Do not refer to the FAB as an icon, according to MS Manual of Style." flag="done"?>button<?oxy_comment_end?>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Name</emphasis> field, type the legend
                    name.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>(Optional) In the <emphasis role="bold">Code</emphasis> field, assign a
                    code.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Create the legend items you want to have in your legend:</para>
                <orderedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Select <emphasis role="bold">Start value</emphasis> and <emphasis
                                role="bold">End value</emphasis>.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Select <emphasis role="bold">Number of
                                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160921T163330+0200" comment="Give feedback to SME: call it Number of legend items
Feedback given to SME 22 sep 2016"?>items<?oxy_comment_end?></emphasis>.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Select a color
                            <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160921T154150+0200" comment="Verify with SME the correct term for this" flag="done"?>scheme<?oxy_comment_end?>.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Create legend items</emphasis>.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </orderedlist>
                <tip>
                    <para>Click the options menu to edit or delete a legend item.</para>
                </tip>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>(Optional) Add more legend items:</para>
                <orderedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Click the add button</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Enter a name and select a start value, an end value and a
                            color.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">OK</emphasis>.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </orderedlist>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Save</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
        <example>
            <title>Vaccination coverage legends</title>
            <table frame="all">
                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160921T162540+0200" comment="Verify how empty title tag renders, should be enough with the example tag."?>
                <title/>
                <?oxy_comment_end?>
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                    <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                    <colspec colname="c3" colnum="3" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>Legend item</entry>
                            <entry>Start value</entry>
                            <entry>End value</entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>Low bad</entry>
                            <entry>0</entry>
                            <entry>50</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>Medium</entry>
                            <entry>50</entry>
                            <entry>80</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>High good</entry>
                            <entry>80</entry>
                            <entry>100</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>Too high</entry>
                            <entry>100</entry>
                            <entry>1000</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </example>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Edit legends</title>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Maintenance</emphasis> app and click <emphasis
                        role="bold">Other</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold"
                    >Legend</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>In the list, find the legend you want to modify.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click the options menu and select <emphasis role="bold"
                    >Edit</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Modify the options you
                    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160510T160124+0200" comment="At next revision, add link to previous section
&quot;For details about each option, refer to section Create a data element.&quot;
At the moment, I can only do x-refs to section 1 tags.
" flag="done"?>want<?oxy_comment_end?>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Save</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Clone legends</title>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Maintenance</emphasis> app and click <emphasis
                        role="bold">Other</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold"
                    >Legend</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>In the list, find the legend you want to clone.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click the options menu and select <emphasis role="bold"
                    >Clone</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Modify the options you
                    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160510T160124+0200" comment="At next revision, add link to previous section
&quot;For details about each option, refer to section Create a data element.&quot;
At the moment, I can only do x-refs to section 1 tags.
" flag="done"?>want<?oxy_comment_end?>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Save</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Delete legends</title>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Maintenance</emphasis> app and click <emphasis
                        role="bold">Other</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold"
                    >Legend</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>In the list, find the legend you want to delete.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click the options menu and select <emphasis role="bold"
                    >Delete</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Confirm</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Display details of legends</title>
        <para/>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Maintenance</emphasis> app and click <emphasis
                        role="bold">Other</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold"
                    >Legend</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>In the list, find the legend you want to view.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click the options menu and select <emphasis role="bold">Show
                        details</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Translate legends</title>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Maintenance</emphasis> app and click <emphasis
                        role="bold">Other</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold"
                    >Legend</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>In the list, find the legend you want to translate.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click the options menu and select <emphasis role="bold"
                    >Translate</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Select a locale.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Type a <emphasis role="bold">Name</emphasis>, <emphasis role="bold">Short
                        name</emphasis> and <emphasis role="bold">Description</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Save</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Assign a legend to indicator or data
            <?oxy_comment_start author="Home" timestamp="20160414T113214+0200" comment="At next revision, add x-ref to relevant topic."?>element<?oxy_comment_end?></title>
        <para>You can assign a legend to an indicator or a data element in the <emphasis role="bold"
                >Maintenance</emphasis> app, either when you create the object or edit it. When you
            then select the indicator or data element in the <emphasis role="bold">GIS</emphasis>
            app, the system automatically selects the assigned legend.</para>
    </section>    
</section>
